{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/posts/Mail-from-Slack-by-OpenFaaS-Cloud","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"57830cd9-7152-5766-ba21-7b94791d2969","html":"<p>In this tutorial I want to show you how I built a function to send emails from a Slack command. It runs for free on OpenFaaS Cloud using the Community Cluster.</p>\n<h2 id=\"openfaas\"><a href=\"#openfaas\" aria-label=\"openfaas permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>OpenFaaS</h2>\n<p>OpenFaaS (Function as a service) is a framework for creating serverless functions on Kubernetes or Docker. It made serverless functions simple. You can run OpenFaaS anywhere on your laptop, your own premise hardware or create a cluster in the cloud. OpenFaaS supporting any language such as GO, Java, Python, C#, Ruby , ASP.NET Core or anything else.\nIf you are new with OpenFaaS workshop is a great place to start.To learn more about OpenFaaS please checkout the project documentation.</p>\n<h2 id=\"openfaas-cloud\"><a href=\"#openfaas-cloud\" aria-label=\"openfaas cloud permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>OpenFaaS Cloud</h2>\n<p>Run you serverless functions using automates CI/CD. You are able to run OpenFaaS cloud self-hosted or use the hosted Community Cluster.</p>\n<h2 id=\"pre-requisites\"><a href=\"#pre-requisites\" aria-label=\"pre requisites permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Pre-requisites</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Access to the OpenFaaS Cloud: Community Cluster, or your own self-hosted cluster with ofc-bootstrap.</li>\n<li>Slack Account.</li>\n<li>You already have faas-cli installed.</li>\n<li>You have an GitHub repository connected to OpenFaaS Cloud: Community Cluster</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"scenario\"><a href=\"#scenario\" aria-label=\"scenario permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Scenario</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Using Slash Command in Slack to send message to an API.</li>\n<li>Use OpenFaaS function as API to receive message from Slack.</li>\n<li>Verifying Slack message HMAC.</li>\n<li>Extract the message.</li>\n<li>Convert message body from Markdown to HTML.</li>\n<li>Send email using nodemailer.</li>\n<li>Send back appropriate message to Slack.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"continue-reading-on-medium\"><a href=\"#continue-reading-on-medium\" aria-label=\"continue reading on medium permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Continue reading on <a href=\"https://medium.com/red-gold/mail-from-slack-by-openfaas-6eeee2228cec\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Medium</a>.</h3>","fields":{"slug":"/posts/Mail-from-Slack-by-OpenFaaS-Cloud","tagSlugs":["/tag/cloud/","/tag/openfaas/","/tag/slack/","/tag/serverless/","/tag/nodejs/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2019-08-31T22:12:03.284Z","description":"In this tutorial I want to show you how I built a function to send emails from a Slack command. It runs for free on OpenFaaS Cloud using the Community Cluster.","tags":["Cloud","Openfaas","Slack","Serverless","Nodejs"],"title":"Mail from Slack by OpenFaaS Cloud","socialImage":"https://miro.medium.com/max/3200/1*SGjfIeI33mRxZp8dBoPzCQ.png"}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/posts/Mail-from-Slack-by-OpenFaaS-Cloud"}}}